Feature: Plant management API

  Background:
    Given Admin logged-in with username "admin" and password "admin123"

  Scenario: Verify create plant with duplicate name
    And Admin sets the endpoint "/api/plants/category/5"
    When Admin sends POST request with payload
      """
      {
        "name": "Rose",
        "price": 100,
        "quantity": 20
      }
      """
    Then Response status code should be 400
    And Response body should match JSON structure
      """
      {
        "status": 400,
        "error": "DUPLICATE_RESOURCE",
        "message": "Plant 'Rose' already exists in this category",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-04T10:05:11.9163253"
      }
      """

  Scenario: Verify create plant with valid data
    And Admin sets the endpoint "/api/plants/category/5"
    When Admin sends POST request with payload
      """
      {
        "name": "Rose",
        "price": 100,
        "quantity": 20
      }
      """
    Then Response status code should be 201
    And Response body should match JSON structure
      """
      {
        "id": 50,
        "name": "Rose",
        "price": 100,
        "quantity": 20,
        "category": {
          "id": 5,
          "name": "FFF",
          "subCategories": []
        }
      }
      """

  Scenario: Verify create plant with missing mandatory fields
    And Admin sets the endpoint "/api/plants/category/1"
    When Admin sends POST request with payload
      """
      {
        "name": "Rose",
        "price": 100
      }
      """
    Then Response status code should be 400
    And Response body should match JSON structure
      """
      {
        "details": {
          "quantity": "Quantity is required"
        },
        "error": "BAD_REQUEST",
        "message": "Validation failed",
        "status": 400,
        "timestamp": "any_non_empty_string"
      }
      """

  Scenario: Verify create plant with negative price
    And Admin sets the endpoint "/api/plants/category/1"
    When Admin sends POST request with payload
      """
      {
        "name": "Rose",
        "price": -100,
        "quantity": 25
      }
      """
    Then Response status code should be 400
    And Response body should match JSON structure
      """
      {
        "details": {
          "quantity": "Quantity cannot be negative"
        },
        "error": "BAD_REQUEST",
        "message": "Validation failed",
        "status": 400,
        "timestamp": "2026-02-04T11:10:02.9029542"
      }
      """

pattern.source: Response body should be an array with {int} items
{word} logs in with username {string} and password {string}
Response body should match JSON structure
The "Add a Plant" button should be visible
Provide {string} plantName {string}, select category {string}, price as {string}, and quantity as {string} for ui
User see an error message as {string}
User see a success message as {string}
The page {string} should be currently active
User clicks {string} button in the action of first record
User see the current details of the plant
User should be on the {string} page
The plant {string} should not be in the list
Only plants with category {string} should be displayed
The plant {string} should be visible in the results
Plants with quantity below 5 should display the {string} badge across all pages
user navigates to edit category page
category list table should be visible
Add Category button should be visible and enabled
the user provide credentials with username {string} and password {string} and click the login button for ui
User should be redirected to the dashboard
